Use Case: Use standalone
Actor(s): User
Purpose: User runs the program and uses it to edit, save, and print equations
-------------------------
Description: 

User loads the program and opens an equation saved on disk. User makes changes
to the equation interactively and saves it back to disk.

Alternative courses:

1. User prints the equation before saving it.

2. User opens the equation directly (e.g., from a file manager) rather than
loading the program first.

3. User downloads the equation from the web with a browser and the equation
editor is opened automatically

-------------------------
Type: primary, domain oriented

Cross References: 

